08:25.000 --> 08:32.000
Primarily the markets would be in the steam generation of electricity.

08:32.000 --> 08:37.000
Perhaps in Florida or even places that are where they use gas at the present time?

08:38.000 --> 08:48.000
Yes sir, Florida right now is a large consumer of Tennessee and Kentucky coal for its generation of electricity.

08:48.000 --> 08:53.000
We visualize that coal will remain competitive in that area.

08:53.000 --> 09:06.000
As we all know there is a great deal of coal in the Cumberland section of Kentucky and Tennessee which we hope will be subject to being barged on the Cumberland River.

09:07.000 --> 09:17.000
This east and middle Tennessee section has a great deal of coal so there is northern Alabama and of course western Kentucky is rich in coal.

09:17.000 --> 09:21.000
So you do envision a great deal of coal traffic down to the Gulf.

09:21.000 --> 09:24.000
Very great potential yes sir.

09:24.000 --> 09:29.000
And then how about from the Gulf back north among the waterway?

09:29.000 --> 09:40.000
Apparently a waterway of this nature inherently lends itself to the movement of both commodities and probably the most significant is petroleum products.

09:40.000 --> 09:52.000
Well what of course benefit consumers along the waterway by virtue of less expensive transportation of heating fuels and gasoline?

09:52.000 --> 10:03.000
